
Linux VLAN Aware Forwarder

This directory contains source code for a linux kernel 
loadable module. This loadable module implements forwarding
functions including dynamic and static mac address support,
ageing of dynamic mac address entries, and shared VLAN learning.

In order to load the forwarder, used the "insmod" command, i.e.
"insmod ipifwd" or "insmod /usr/src/linux-XXX/net/ipifwd/ipifwd.o"
The forwarder may be unloaded using the "rmmod" command.

Fri Jul 11 10:34:03 EDT 2003

This release of the forwarder does not support the optional replacement
of dynamic filtering entries upon the filtering table beoming full.


